techmeme.title: Instacart reports Q3 revenue up 12% YoY to $852M, vs. $843.6M est., gross transaction value up 11% to $8.3B, and forecasts Q4 adjusted EBITDA below estimates (Natalie Lung/Bloomberg)
Spotify reports Q3 revenue up 19% YoY to €3.99B, vs. €4.02B est., MAUs up 11% to 640M, and forecasts Q4 profit and MAUs above est.; SPOT jumps 8%+ after hours (Jaspreet Singh/Reuters)
Sources: Apple is making a 6" wall-mounted display that can control appliances, do videoconferencing, and use AI to navigate apps, and may unveil it by March (Mark Gurman/Bloomberg)
US gov't data: 669 of 1,089 approved H-1B hires for TikTok and ByteDance from Oct. 2022 to Sept. 2023 were from China, up 50% YoY, despite US lawmaker scrutiny (Dan Whateley/Business Insider)
Source: Elon Musk's America PAC spent ~$200M to help elect Trump; Musk says the PAC is gearing up for midterms as well as judicial and DA elections (Dan Merica/Associated Press)
